                Pasting here since Im in an airport

3. do `ioreg -l -w0 | grep Capacity`:
 | | â€œAppleRawCurrentCapacityâ€ = 6705
| | â€œAppleRawMaxCapacityâ€ = 6705
| | â€œMaxCapacityâ€ = 6705
| | â€œCurrentCapacityâ€ = 6705
| | â€œLegacyBatteryInfoâ€ = {â€œAmperageâ€=0,â€Flagsâ€=5,â€Capacityâ€=6705,â€Currentâ€=6705,â€Voltageâ€=8517,â€œCycle Countâ€=160}
| | â€œBatteryDataâ€ = {â€œStateOfChargeâ€=100,â€PMUConfiguredâ€=0,â€CellVoltageâ€=(4261,4256),â€AdapterPowerâ€=784,â€LifetimeDataâ€={â€œUpdateTimeâ€=1637173843},â€SystemPowerâ€=1321,â€Serialâ€=â€-â€œ,â€DesignCapacityâ€=7150,â€CycleCountâ€=160,â€Voltageâ€=8518,â€Qmaxâ€=(7213,7160)}
| | â€œDesignCapacityâ€ = 7150

4. Calculate Battery Health using simple maths:

â€œDesign Capacityâ€ represents 100%
â€œMax Capacityâ€ is x (Battery Health).
The result is x = (â€œMax Capacityâ€ x 100) / Design Capacity = (6705 x 100) / 7150 = 93.77%

